=== AUTHENTICATION / SESSION POLICY ANALYSIS ===

AUTH PROVIDER: Supabase Auth (JWT-based)
SESSION MODEL: JWT tokens stored in cookies via @supabase/ssr

TOKEN EXPIRY:
- Supabase default: 1 hour access token, 7 day refresh token
- No custom expiry configuration found in codebase
- Token refresh handled by Supabase client library automatically
- ISSUE: No server-side session revocation mechanism found
  (Supabase JWTs are valid until expiry even after signOut)

IDLE TIMEOUT:
- Implementation: lib/auth/idle-timeout.ts — 30 minutes (NIST 800-63B compliant)
- Component: components/auth/IdleTimeoutGuard.tsx
- ISSUE: Only used in app/lms/(app)/layout.tsx
  - Admin portal: NO idle timeout — HIGH
  - Instructor portal: NO idle timeout — HIGH
  - Staff portal: NO idle timeout — HIGH
  - Workforce board: NO idle timeout — HIGH
- ISSUE: Client-side only enforcement — can be bypassed by disabling JavaScript
  - No server-side session timeout enforcement

PASSWORD POLICY:
- Minimum 8 characters — GOOD (NIST 800-63B)
- Common password blocklist (25 entries) — GOOD but small
- No composition rules (per NIST recommendation) — GOOD
- Sequential/repeated character check — GOOD
- ISSUE: Password validation only enforced client-side in signup forms
  - app/api/auth/signup/route.ts only checks length >= 8, not full validation
  - No server-side common password check
  - No breached password database check (NIST recommends HIBP integration)

AUTH GUARD PATTERNS:
- Server-side: requireAdmin(), requireAuth(), requireRole() in lib/auth.ts — GOOD
- Client-side: useEffect + supabase.auth.getUser() in LMS layout — WEAK
- API routes: Mix of getSession(), getAuthUser(), createClient() — INCONSISTENT
- Demo mode: isDemoMode() returns false always — GOOD (disabled)

SEVERITY:
- HIGH: Idle timeout only in LMS, not admin/instructor/staff portals
- HIGH: Client-side only idle timeout (no server enforcement)
- MEDIUM: Password validation not fully enforced server-side
- MEDIUM: No server-side session revocation
- LOW: Small common password blocklist
